2011-12-02T05:30:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/philippine-stocks-movers-san-miguel-brewery-san-miguel-corp-.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual (PCOMP)  moves in  Philippine (PASHR)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index added less than 0.1
percent to 4,290.92. The gauge rose 0.7 percent this week, the
first gain in three weeks.  Easycall Communications Philippines Inc. (ECP)   dropped
5.3 percent to 1.80 pesos, the lowest since Nov. 16. The public
now owns 10.1 percent of the company after Easycall shareholder
Global e-Business Solutions Inc. sold 8 million shares, the
company said in a disclosure to the exchange.  San Miguel Brewery Inc. (SMB)   rose 1.8 percent to 29
pesos, its highest close since Nov. 23, as it seeks changes in
the terms of 38.8 billion pesos ($897 million) of bonds sold in
2009. The company wants a so-called minimum interest coverage
ratio to replace the minimum current ratio for the bonds.  San Miguel Corp. (SMC)   dropped 2.5 percent to 120 pesos,
its lowest close since Nov. 15. The nationâ€™s largest listed
company by sales said in an exchange filing that shareholder Top
Frontier Investment Holdings Inc. sold 9 million common shares
yesterday. Philippine Stock Exchange data showed a block of nine
million shares were sold at 119.12 pesos each.  To contact the reporter on this story:
